tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits, including glucose and HbA1c, indicating good glycemic control. Renal function (urea, creatinine) and electrolytes are normal. No laboratory evidence of metabolic or renal dysfunction at this time. No further action required from a laboratory perspective.
